node.text:
It’s almost 2021 and while I can’t wait to say goodbye to 2020, it’s also left me thinking about goals for 2021. I think it’s important to believe in the magic of a new year. A clean, fresh start. But this year I’ve encouraged my kids to do realizations instead of resolutions. I think it seems healthier, allows for more personal growth, and still helps you set sustainable goals.  It’s more about the journey and less about the destination. More about what you’re learning and how experiences (bad or good) encourage that growth. Versus always feeling bad when we don’t hit every goal we set for ourselves. 
What do you think? Do you prefer resolutions or realizations? What are your realizations from 2020?

No braiding required for this super simple fishtail braid! 
Step 1: spray some @hairitagebymindy dry shampoo to add a little grip to hair
Step 2: split hair into two pieces 
Step 3: split off one small piece on outside edge and cross over top and add into other large section
Step 4: repeat on other side
Step 5: repeat over and over until you run out of hair. Secure with an elastic
Step 6: apply @hairitagebymindy magic dust and then pancake the braid to make it large and puffy! 
@brooklynandbailey

⭐️JUNETEENTH⭐️ 

 Also know as Jubilee Day or Black Independence Day, Juneteenth was started near Galveston TX as a celebration of the day all enslaved people were finally set free! 

Despite Lincoln issuing the Emancipation Proclamation 1862, it took almost three years for federal troops to reach isolated areas in Texas and on June 19, 1865 the last enslaved people were finally freed❤️ 

This year is especially sweet because last week Juneteenth became a nationally recognized federal holiday! 

I’m grateful for my interracial family and the growth we experience together and plan to continue to do and be better for them❤️

Swipe to see some family fun

node.text:
New headshots who dis? 

If you know me at all you know I HATE photo shoots even though I have to do them a lot for work. It’s always so strange standing alone in front of a whole room of people trying to make my poses look cute and not awkward 🤣 it’s like putting all my insecurities on display for everyone to see. 

But this shoot I felt like a boss…powerful on the outside and inside 💪🏻 The last few years I definitely feel like I’ve found my stride both in work and family life. Although I’m still a work in progress, it is so fun to look at these photos and feel strong, intelligent, secure in my femininity, and comfortable being exactly who I am. 

Thanks to @slybeautycosmetics on h/m and @jessyjphoto on 📸 for making me feel amazing!
